B.4 Contact Resistivity Fitting Details

Data from Gao et al. (2026b) were digitized using WebPlotDigitizer. The measured time constants \tau_{\text{NI}} at various operating currents were converted to contact resistivity using \tau_{\text{NI}} = L/(R_c) with R_c = \rho_{ct}/(2\pi R_{\text{mean}} w)\,N_t N_p. The coil inductance L was computed from geometry. The fitted parameters were obtained via non‑linear least squares (Levenberg‑Marquardt). Residuals showed no systematic trend; the standard deviation of residuals was 8% of the measured values.

